19. Philoctetam. He possessed the bow and poisoned arrows of Hercules. In consequence of an oracle, which declared that Troy could not be taken without those weapons, the Greeks brought him as far as Lemnos, where they were compelled to leave him, on ac- count of a noisome wound in one of his feet. After ten years of tortum, he was removed from the island by Ulysses, after the death of Achilles.
